1. Which Agile principle was easiest to implement using Taiga?
The easiest Agile principle to implement using Taiga was welcoming changing requirements. 
Taigaâ€™s backlog allows new user stories to be added and priorities to be changed easily without affecting completed work.

2. Which principle was difficult to represent using a tool?
The principle that was difficult to represent using a tool was individuals and interactions
over processes and tools. This principle depends more on human communication than on software features.

3. How does Taiga support collaboration and transparency?
Taiga supports collaboration and transparency by showing user stories,
backlog, sprint boards, and comments to all team members. Everyone can see progress, changes, and responsibilities clearly.

4. Can Agile values exist without tools? Justify.
Yes, Agile values can exist without tools because Agile is a mindset focused on teamwork, communication, and flexibility.
Tools like Taiga help manage work but are not mandatory to follow Agile values.
